					<br /><b>Joined:</b> Mon Sep 27, 2004 8:33 am<br /><b>Posts:</b> 3711<br /><b>Location:</b> Central Texas, USA
				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Emulation accuracy is often referred to as if the entire emulator must be to the same accuracy. This is no the case; parts of the emulator can be more or less accurate than other parts. Few games need mid-scanline <em>rendering</em> accuracy, but many games need mid-scanline accuracy for PPU status register readsand scroll registers. Emulating cycle-accurate PPU rendering is significantly more complex than just emulating $2002, $2005, and $2006 accurately and rendering graphics with only scanline accuracy.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
